summary:
Tundra Swans by PVS.   oil on canvas 24x30.   

with a full belly of turkey gumbo and a glass of wine, I finished this painting...
caption: Tundra Swans by PVS.   oil on canvas 24x30.    with a full belly of turkey gumbo and a glass of wine, I finished this painting of a wedge of swans (they were in a wedge–this is the tail end) as they left the lake below my house which sits up on a ridge on the south side of the lake.  We had just had a dust of snow and I caught a quick snapshot early morning from my studio window.  These are tundra swans and migrate from above the Arctic Circle to winter in the Chesapeake Bay.  They travel nearly 3000 miles at an average speed of 50 mph.  They will often stop here for a day or two before heading on.  They are quite noisy.  God gives little blessings every now and then.  Oil on canvas 24x30.
